cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about improving sequence labeling models using character-level extensions and an attention mechanism. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also proposes a novel architecture for combining word- and character-level representations, which involves machine learning techniques such as attention mechanisms and neural networks. This suggests that the paper could also belong to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed architecture on sequence labeling datasets, which could also place it in the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), which often involves sequence labeling tasks such as object recognition and tracking.
